description: Measure the voltage at both the input and output terminals (+ and −) of Control Module 5 to determine if voltage is still present, and to locate where the voltage drop or interruption occurs across the control module series., outcome='Voltage at both the input and output (+) terminals of Control Module 5 is 11.9893 V with respect to ground, and voltage at both (−) terminals is 0.0 V. There is no significant voltage drop across Control Module 5; voltage is present and nominal at the input and output terminals.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module 6 Input and Output Terminals,
description: Measure the voltage at both the input and output terminals (+ and −) of Control Module 6 to verify if voltage is still present, helping to pinpoint where the voltage interruption occurs between the modules and the load., outcome='Control Input Cable (+) 6 shows a voltage of 11.9893 V with respect to ground, while Control Input Cable (−) 6 reads 0.0 V. Both Control Output Cable (+) 6 and Control Output Cable (−) 6 also measure 0.0 V. This indicates that voltage is present at the input terminals but absent at the output terminals of Control Module 6.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control Module 6 internal circuitry,
description: Open the inspection panel of Control Module 6 and visually inspect the internal circuit, especially for clear signs of damage, loose connections, or components that may have failed (burnt resistor, disconnected or broken wire, dislodged or missing LED)., outcome="Inspection indicates that Control Cube 6's green power flow indicator LED and its associated resistor are both physically missing and cannot be replaced. No observable internal faults or damage were found in the switch or connected cables. All relevant cables appear securely connected, with no polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=85.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
